> Will the memory be released back to kernel if the big file is read and results computed by forking
> a child process? Since the child process dies after executing the last line of ruby code passed
> as a block to fork.


Your question is a bit ambiguous regarding the event ordering.  The file read has to occur in the child process, not the parent.  When the child is done, it exits returning any memory used back to the kernel.  Meanwhile the parent can handle/dispatch new jobs to new children.

Gary Wright
